quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  72,1,"Say, “It has been revealed to me that a company of jinn listened and they said, “ ‘We have indeed heard a wonderful recital"
  72,2,"“ ‘It gives guidance to the right way, and we believe in it. We will not join any with our Lord"
  72,3,“ ‘And Exalted is the Majesty of our Lord. He has neither wife nor child
  72,4,“ ‘There were some foolish ones among us who used to speak elaborate lies against God
  72,5,“ ‘But we think that no human nor jinn should say anything that is untrue about God
  72,6,"“ ‘True, there were men among the humans who sought refuge with men among the jinn, and they increased them in being unwise"
  72,7,"“ ‘They think, as you thought, that God would not raise up anyone"
  72,8,"“ ‘And we pried into the secrets of heaven, but we found it filled with stern guards and flaming fires"
  72,9,"“ ‘We used to sit there in position to listen, but any who listen now will find a flaming fire watching them in ambush"
  72,10,"“ ‘And we do not understand whether harm is intended to those on earth, or whether their Lord intends to guide them to right conduct"
  72,11,"“ ‘There are among us some who are righteous, and some who are not. We follow different paths"
  72,12,"“ ‘But we know that by no means can we stop God throughout the earth, nor can we stop Him by flight"
  72,13,"“ ‘And as for us, since we have listened to the guidance, we have accepted it, and any who believes in his Lord has no fear, loss, nor burden"